<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-US">
<head>
  {{ template "head" . }}

  {{/* TODO: Is this next script actually needed? */}}
  <script>
    window.summaryData = {{ .JSON }};
  </script>
</head>

<body class="layoutSidebar">
  <header class="layoutSidebar__sidebar">
    {{ template "navbar" "--stack" }}

    <nav>
      <ul class="navList" role="list">
        <li>
          <a class="linkIcon" href="/">
            <i aria-hidden="true" class="fas fa-fw fa-list-ul"></i>
            List All Namespaces
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a class="linkIcon" href="/dashboard">
            <i aria-hidden="true" class="far fa-fw fa-eye"></i>
            Detail All Namespaces
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a class="linkIcon" href="#glossary">
            <i aria-hidden="true" class="fas fa-fw fa-book"></i>
            Glossary
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    {{ if gt (len .Data.Namespaces) 1 }}
    <form aria-controls="js-filter-container" id="js-filter-form" role="search">
      <label class="visually-hidden" for="namespace-search">Filter namespaces</label>

      <input aria-controls="js-filter-container" name="q" placeholder="Filter Namespaces..." type="search" />

      <button type="submit">
        <i aria-hidden="true" class="fas fa-fw fa-search"></i>
        <span class="visually-hidden">Search</span>
      </button>
    </form>
    {{ end }}
  </header>

  <div class="layoutSidebar__main">
    <main class="verticalRhythm --rhythm-3">
      <h1>Namespace Details</h1>

      <div
        {{ if gt (len .Data.Namespaces) 1 }}
        aria-live="off"
        id="js-filter-container"
        {{ end }}
      >
        {{ range $nsName, $nsSummary := .Data.Namespaces }}
          {{ template "namespace" $nsSummary }}
        {{end}}
      </div>

      <aside class="verticalRhythm" id="glossary">
        <h2>Glossary</h2>

        <dl>
          <div class="dl-entry">
            <dt id="qos">QoS</dt>
            <dd>
              <blockquote>
                "QoS (Quality of Service) class is a designation assigned to a pod based on its resource requests and limits. Kubernetes uses QoS classes to make decisions about scheduling and evicting Pods."
                <cite><a class="--link-1" href="https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/quality-service-pod" target="_blank">Kubernetes Documentation: <br>Configure Quality of Service for Pods <i aria-label="(Opens in new window)" class="fas fa-fw fa-external-link-alt"></i></a></cite>
              </blockquote>
            </dd>
          </div>

          <div class="dl-entry">
            <dt>Guaranteed QoS</dt>
            <dd>
              <blockquote>
                "For a Pod to be given a QoS class of Guaranteed:
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    Every Container, including init containers, in the Pod must have a memory limit and a memory request, and they must be the same.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Every Container, including init containers, in the Pod must have a CPU limit and a CPU request, and they must be the same."
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <cite><a class="--link-1" href="https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/quality-service-pod/#create-a-pod-that-gets-assigned-a-qos-class-of-guaranteed" target="_blank">Kubernetes Documentation: <br>Create a Pod That Gets Assigned a QoS Class of Guaranteed <i aria-label="(Opens in new window)" class="fas fa-fw fa-external-link-alt"></i></a></cite>
              </blockquote>
            </dd>
          </div>

          <div class="dl-entry">
            <dt>Burstable QoS</dt>
            <dd>
              <blockquote>
                "A Pod is given a QoS class of Burstable if:
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    The Pod does not meet the criteria for QoS class Guaranteed.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    At least one Container in the Pod has a memory or CPU request."
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <cite><a class="--link-1" href="https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/quality-service-pod/#create-a-pod-that-gets-assigned-a-qos-class-of-burstable" target="_blank">Kubernetes Documentation: <br>Create a Pod That Gets Assigned a QoS Class of Burstable <i aria-label="(Opens in new window)" class="fas fa-fw fa-external-link-alt"></i></a></cite>
              </blockquote>
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </aside>
    </main>

    <footer>
      {{ template "footer" . }}
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
